{%- comment -%} snippets/win95-volume.liquid — Win98 volume control for the taskbar tray. {%- endcomment -%}
<div class="jj-vol-tray" id="jj-vol-tray">
  <button type="button" class="jj-vol-btn" id="jj-vol-btn" aria-label="Volume" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="jj-vol-popup">
    {%- comment -%} Pixel-art speaker (13px grid, crispEdges) — driver box,
        stepped cone, two pixel wave arcs. Scanline dither + phosphor glow
        live in CSS (.jj-vol-btn__icon / svg). {%- endcomment -%}
    <span class="jj-vol-btn__icon" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 13 13" width="13" height="13" shape-rendering="crispEdges">
        <path fill="currentColor" d="M1 4h2v5h-2z M3 3h1v7h-1z M4 2h1v9h-1z"></path>
        <path class="jj-vol-wave" fill="currentColor" d="M6 4h1v1h-1z M7 5h1v3h-1z M6 8h1v1h-1z M8 2h1v1h-1z M9 3h1v1h-1z M10 4h1v5h-1z M9 9h1v1h-1z M8 10h1v1h-1z"></path>
      </svg>
      <span class="jj-vol-btn__x" aria-hidden="true">×</span>
    </span>
  </button>
  {%- comment -%} Win98 mixer layout (sound.png ref): Volume title, loudness
      wedge beside the slider, dotted keyboard-focus box around the slider
      column, Mute checkbox with its access-key underline. {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="jj-vol-popup" id="jj-vol-popup" role="dialog" aria-label="Volume" hidden>
    <div class="jj-vol-popup__title" aria-hidden="true">Volume</div>
    <div class="jj-vol-popup__body">
      <div class="jj-vol-wedge" aria-hidden="true"><div class="jj-vol-wedge__fill"></div></div>
      <div class="jj-vol-well">
        <input type="range" class="jj-vol-slider" id="jj-vol-slider" min="0" max="100" value="80" step="1" aria-label="Volume level">
      </div>
    </div>
    <label class="jj-vol-mute"><input type="checkbox" id="jj-vol-mute-cb"> <span><u>M</u>ute</span></label>
  </div>
</div>
